race.comment: MASTER ALEX (2) was snagged back from a wide gate when resuming and hit the line full of running for third over a shorter trip. Strips fitter, drawn better, and looks perfectly placed to get the job done. NEVER SOBER (7) has found his rhythm again, racing up on speed and sticking on well. Another honest effort here last time and he won't need to lift much to feature. KEYTRADE (1) led them up before being collared late last start. Forgive run, he's better than that and the claim helps offset the weight. Can bounce back. BENTLEY BEAU (6) found the line well fresh and should be fitter for that. Capable of running on into the minors. PULL THE TRIGGER (3) hasn't shown his best lately but loves it here and could surprise if things fall into place.
